&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Architect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Remote (U.S.) / Travel onsite to dealerships is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule: &lt;/strong&gt;Standard business hours, aligned to assigned dealership accounts and time zones.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Numa&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Numa is building the platform to power AI-native dealerships, rearchitecting automotive service and sales with advanced AI agents that automate customer interactions, streamline operations, and reimagine how dealerships work. Numa integrates AI into every aspect of dealership functions—from rescuing customer calls and voicemails that generate more revenue, to reducing customer resolution times that drive overall customer satisfaction (CSI), to improving dealership team productivity and accountability. Numa has raised $50 million from leading investors (Google, Threshold, Costanoa, Mitsui, and Touring Capital).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Performance Architect to join our team and serve as a strategic, consultative partner to the dealerships we serve. In this role, you will act as a trusted advisor to dealership leadership, connecting Numa’s platform to each customer’s core business goals and translating performance data into measurable outcomes, retention, and expansion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of multiple teams—including Customer Success, Product, and Sales—and acts as a key “connector” between the dealership and Numa. Success in this role requires someone who deeply understands dealership operations, can lead executive-level conversations with credibility, and can tie a software platform to operational KPIs and business priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a former General Manager, Fixed Operations Director, or similar dealership leader who knows what it takes to run a profitable, high-performing service department. You take initiative, build trust quickly, and are comfortable owning executive relationships and driving forward-looking action plans without heavy direction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strategic partnerships with dealership GMs and leadership teams, earning trust through insight, credibility, and results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tie Numa’s platform to business goals such as profit, team productivity, and customer satisfaction (CSI)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead executive Quarterly Business Reviews (QBRs) that align teams and create forward-looking action plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver dealership-specific performance insights that are actionable, impactful, and aligned with local priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and manage 90-day engagement plans that drive measurable outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide strategic reviews and tailor action plans based on real-time performance metrics and dealership priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Elevate Numa from a vendor to a strategic partner that leadership relies on for results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with Product, Customer Success, and Sales to shape tools, playbooks, and best practices that elevate client success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel onsite to dealerships as needed to deepen relationships and drive engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep experience in automotive, including time on both the dealer and vendor side&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as a former General Manager, Fixed Operations Director, or similar leadership role within a dealership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to run and grow a service department, including driving profitability and customer satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
